## Project Overview
Building a social network that combines features from X/Twitter and Reddit.

## stack
- NextJs
- PostgreSQL + Prisma

## Core Features
- User account system
- Post creation and sharing
- Feed browsing and customization
- Voting system (upvote/downvote)
- Commenting system
- Community-based organization

## System Entities

### Users
- Must have an account to participate
- Can create posts and comments
- Can customize their feeds

### Posts
- Can be posted globally (default behaviour), in specific communities, or privately (to followers only)
- Can be upvoted or downvoted with visible ratio
- Support multiple languages (default: English)
- Can be commented on

### Comments
- Can be upvoted/downvoted
- Sorted by upvote/downvote ratio
- Attached to posts

### Communities
- Theme-related areas pretty similar to subreddits
- Can be created by every users
- users can join the communities
- can be private or public

### Feeds
- Customizable feeds where users can add specific users, and/or communities
- Similar to Twitter lists or Reddit custom feeds